(a) instead of using a concrete substantive qualined by adjective or partic„ Tacitus osten employs an abstract substantive coupled with a concrete in the ‘defining' genitive: obiectus molium, for moles obiectas, xiv 8, 2 ; contrario sagittarum iactu, xv 9, 1 (=sagittis ex adverso iactis) ; communione parietum, xv 43, 4.
